==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Regurgitation
<hw>Re*gur`gi*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(-t?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧gurgitation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
flowing or pouring back by the orifice of entrance</def>; specifically
<fld>(Med.)</fld>, <def>the reversal of the natural direction in which
the current or contents flow through a tube or cavity of the body.</def>
<rj><au>Quain.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of swallowing again; reabsorption.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rehabilitate</ent>⟦br⟧
